==Demographics==
As of the 2020 census, there were 320 people, 77 housing units, and 17 families in the CDP. There were 18 [[White Americans|White]] people, 0 [[African Americans]], 280 [[Native Americans in the United States|Native Americans]], 9 people from some other race, and 13 people from two or more races. 17 people were of [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] origin.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web |title=Explore Census Data |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/Qui-nai-elt_Village_CDP;_Washington?g=160XX00US5357030 |access-date=2023-05-22 |website=data.census.gov}}</ref>

The median age was 52.5 years old. 10.2% of the population spoke [[Spanish language|Spanish]] at home. 22.4% of the population were older than 65, 10.2% from 65 to 74, and 12.2% from 75 to 84.<ref name=":0" />

The median household income was $87,917, with families having $53,750. 0.0% of the population were in poverty.<ref name=":0" />

